tAcknowledgements -- tAbout the Author and Illustrator0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  a“Make yourself big when you enter a room, when you meet a bear in the woods. Make yourself big. Meet the eyes.” Roger Epp’s poetic meditations about the best, the hardest, the loneliest times of leading a small university campus through significant change are depicted in a series of elegant yet understated prose pieces, alongside images by his life partner, Rhonda Harder Epp. Taking a candid look at the many challenges such a position brings, Roger Epp humanizes, scrutinizes, and upholds the integrity of academic administrative work. Only Leave a Trace will resonate with those who work in universities, hold leadership roles in them, or care about the connections between higher education, students, and place.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAdministration scolaire. 0aEducational leadershipvPoetry. 0aEducational leadership. 0aLeadership en éducation. 0aSchool management and organizationvPoetry. 0aSchool management and organization. 7aSELF-HELP / Personal Growth / General.2bisacsh  aLeadership / Meditations.1 aHarder Epp, Rhonda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212314240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772123142423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772123142/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles